This formula will be crucial in the reconstruction formula in the Nyquist-Shannon Theorem. Note: One should not try to evaluate <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi>τ</m:mi><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>Δ</m:mi><m:mi>τ</m:mi></m:msub><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>; indeed, it is not really a function, since it is formed
by Dirac terms. Even its power is infinite.
